fdryMacVlanGlobalClearOper.name: fdryMacVlanGlobalClearOper
fdryMacVlanGlobalClearOper.description: valid(0) - this value is always returned when the variable is read. clear(1) - setting the variable to this value clears the operational MAC-based VLAN information for all ports.

fdryMacVlanGlobalDynConfigState.name: fdryMacVlanGlobalDynConfigState
fdryMacVlanGlobalDynConfigState.description: Enable/disable MAC-based VLAN dynamic activation on the global level.

fdryMacVlanPortMemberEntry.name: fdryMacVlanPortMemberEntry
fdryMacVlanPortMemberEntry.description: An entry of the MAC-based VLAN port membership table.

fdryMacVlanPortMemberPortId.name: fdryMacVlanPortMemberPortId
fdryMacVlanPortMemberPortId.description: The ifIndex of the port which is a member of the MAC-based VLAN.

fdryMacVlanPortMemberRowStatus.name: fdryMacVlanPortMemberRowStatus
fdryMacVlanPortMemberRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the table.

fdryMacVlanIfEntry.name: fdryMacVlanIfEntry
fdryMacVlanIfEntry.description: An entry in the MAC-based VLAN interface table.

fdryMacVlanIfIndex.name: fdryMacVlanIfIndex
fdryMacVlanIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface which is a member of the MAC-based VLAN.

fdryMacVlanIfEnable.name: fdryMacVlanIfEnable
fdryMacVlanIfEnable.description: The administrative status requested by management for MAC-based VLANs on this interface. The value enabled(1) indicates that MAC-based VLANs should be enabled on this interface, When disabled(2), MAC-based VLANs are disabled on this interface. Enable/disable MAC-based VLAN on this interface.

fdryMacVlanIfMaxEntry.name: fdryMacVlanIfMaxEntry
fdryMacVlanIfMaxEntry.description: The maximum number of allowed and denied MAC address (static and dynamic) that can be leared on this interface. The default value is 2. The value should be between 2 to 32.

fdryMacVlanIfClearOper.name: fdryMacVlanIfClearOper
fdryMacVlanIfClearOper.description: valid(0) - this value is always returned when the variable is read. clear(1) - setting the variable to this value clears the operational MAC-based VLAN information for a port.

fdryMacVlanIfClearConfig.name: fdryMacVlanIfClearConfig
fdryMacVlanIfClearConfig.description: valid(0) - this value is always returned when the variable is read. clear(1) - setting the variable to this value clears the configured MAC-based VLAN information for a port.

fdryMacBasedVlanEntry.name: fdryMacBasedVlanEntry
fdryMacBasedVlanEntry.description: An entry in the MAC-based VLAN table.

fdryMacBasedVlanId.name: fdryMacBasedVlanId
fdryMacBasedVlanId.description: The VLAN ID for this entry.

fdryMacBasedVlanMac.name: fdryMacBasedVlanMac
fdryMacBasedVlanMac.description: A host source MAC address to be authenticated.

fdryMacBasedVlanPriority.name: fdryMacBasedVlanPriority
fdryMacBasedVlanPriority.description: The priority of the source MAC address.

fdryMacBasedVlanRowStatus.name: fdryMacBasedVlanRowStatus
fdryMacBasedVlanRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the table.
